The Docs repository is a collection of project documentation for Nicholas Tritsaris, automatically generated using ''Groq'' and the ''GitHub API''. This documentation provides an overview of the projects and serves as a navigation hub for exploring the various repositories. The documentation is organized in a way that allows for easy browsing and discovery of project information.

== Overview ==
The Docs repository is designed to provide a centralized location for accessing project documentation. The use of ''Groq'' and the ''GitHub API'' enables automatic generation of the documentation, ensuring that the information is up-to-date and accurate.

== Features ==
The documentation includes features such as automatic generation using ''Groq'' and the ''GitHub API'', providing a convenient and efficient way to manage project documentation. The repository also includes a navigation section that allows users to browse all project repositories.

== Navigation ==
The repository includes a navigation section that provides links to other project repositories, allowing users to easily explore and discover new projects. The navigation section includes a link to [[Projects|Browse all project repositories]], making it easy to find and access project information.

== Installation ==
As the Docs repository is a collection of documentation and not a software application, there is no installation required. Users can access the documentation directly through the repository, and the automatic generation using ''Groq'' and the ''GitHub API'' ensures that the information is always current.